<section xml:id="sec-cleaning-and-recoding-data">
  <title>Cleaning and Recoding Data</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This section covers essential techniques for preparing data for analysis, including cleaning messy data and recoding variables.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Understand the importance of data cleaning</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Learn techniques for identifying and handling data quality issues</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Master variable recoding and transformation</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-data-cleaning-basics">
    <title>Data Cleaning Basics</title>
    <p>
      Data cleaning involves identifying and correcting errors, inconsistencies, and inaccuracies in data. This is a crucial step before any analysis.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-recoding-variables">
    <title>Recoding Variables</title>
    <p>
      Recoding involves transforming variables to make them more suitable for analysis. This might include creating categories from continuous variables or combining categories.
    </p>
  </subsection>

</section>
